## CH1 • DAY 2

.TBA

INT. Local university - Corridors

SAYLOR
So, you’re saying Eddie arrived to this town too.

RICK
Yeah.  And he’s... right behind this door.  Expecting us.

SAYLOR
Do we need to knock?

RICK
No.  It’s Eddie.

They snort with quiet laughter.  RICK opens the door without knocking.

INT. Local university - The secret room

EDDIE, a young, skinny, long-legged student, is lying on a bundle of wires like a hammock.  Most notably, EDDIE wears glasses on his face and a wool vest full of green exclamation points.  This vest is a homage to the Seventh Doctor (Doctor Who).

EDDIE
(scared)
Aaaaah!  Oh, it’s you two.  I always say to everyone, knock on the door!  No matter what!  You never know what I’m up to!

RICK
Look at you, a fashion icon.

EDDIE
(points at the glasses he’s wearing)
Eyes tend to trick me.

SAYLOR
(waves)
Made yourself at home already?

EDDIE
Ah.  A bunch of wires beyond repair.  See?  Scratched, exposed and burnt.  Rick helped me to make them more useful.

RICK
By attaching them to the wall.  We’ve made some holes.  Firmly attached, I made sure these wires didn’t come loose from there.

SAYLOR
Oh that’s quite practical.  A handiwork worthy of praise.

EDDIE
Don’t tell anyone about this little redecoration.  Oh and, close that door.

RICK closes the door behind him and SAYLOR.  EDDIE gets up, takes some wires and walks to the wire sockets.

EDDIE (CONT’D)
So um, work in progress, you need to wait... let’s say...

EDDIE checks the time on his watch on the wrist of his left hand.

EDDIE (CONT’D)
15 minutes!  No, 5 minutes!  2 minutes!

EDDIE abruptly removes the watch and tosses it somewhere away from him without looking.

EDDIE (CONT’D)
1 minute!  Not half an hour.  Half a minute.  Or...

EDDIE quickly connects, reconnects and swaps some wires.  It only takes 5 seconds.

EDDIE (CONT’D)
(looks at SAYLOR and RICK)
Now I’m all ears!

Wire sockets make light explosion and sparks.  EDDIE dodges it but loses his glasses and he’s got a little soot on his cheek.

EDDIE (CONT’D)
Um.  Nevermind that.  Timing issues.  I guess anyone of you has some wet wipe.

SAYLOR rummages through her handbag and, humming “Mm-hm!  Pizzeria”, finds an unopened packet with a wet wipe.  She shows it to EDDIE and throws it at him with a swing.  EDDIE masterfully catches it, he was very close to losing it.  He unpacks a wet wipe and quickly wipes the soot off his cheek.  SAYLOR picks the glasses from the floor.

SAYLOR
You know, you don’t need these glasses anyway.  You’re more handsome now.  A girl’s opinion.

EDDIE
There’s a neverending inner dilemma between that and the professional look.

SAYLOR
Feels like a litmus paper, hm?

EDDIE
(confused)
Whatever it is.

SAYLOR casually puts on the glasses.

SAYLOR
Hey!  They’re zero power!

EDDIE
You didn’t expect augmented reality, right?

RICK
(to SAYLOR)
Give me.

RICK takes the glasses from SAYLOR and puts them on himself.

RICK (CONT’D)
(to EDDIE)
Now.  You know the deal.

Dramatic pause, zooming in on EDDIE.

EDDIE
Wicked.  Let’s get started then.

